page.title: 10ECOLOGY IN HIGHER POYNTON
page.content: The countryside around Higher Poynton is partly wooded and partly open grassland.There are very few people living in the area and so much wildlife can be seen,both animals and birds.Near the entrance to Lyme Park we saw many grey squirrels and rabbits and many birds such as bluetits robins blackbirds and magpies.In the newly made Elmwood Nature Reserve a variety of creatures have made their home including squirrels nuthatches, a fox was seen in the area too.Many types of ducks can be seen on the canal.We also discovered frogspawn and tadpoles in pools on middlewood walkway.Many wild flowers can be found in the wooded areas,such as bluebells, cow parsley wild garlic and campion.
